    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <description>Tutanota is the world's most secure email service, easy to use and private by design. Sign up for free encrypted email now.

With end-to-end encryption and 2FA, your emails have never been more secure. The built-in encryption guarantees that your mailbox belongs to you: Nobody can decrypt or read your data.

**Please Note**: This is an automatically updated package. If you find it is out of date by more than a day or two, please contact the maintainer(s) and let them know the package is no longer updating correctly.</description>
    <summary>Tutanota is an email client with a strong focus on security and privacy that lets you encrypt emails on all your devices.</summary>
    <releaseNotes># What's new
 - Update search indexing UI [#10350](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10350)
 - Implement non-blocking search index extension [#10349](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10349)
 - Allow easy extension of search index range [#10351](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10351)
 - Allow easy index recreation on locally stored data [#10381](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10381)
 - Change default offline range to two years for paid users [#10348](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10348)
 - Update local offline range when indexing is cancelled [#10567](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10567)
 - Allow filtering spam mails in search view [#10521](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10521)
 - Rework search index warning [#10520](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10520)

# Bugfixes
 - Print function can't be triggered [#10628](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10628)
 - Extending the mail index range while already indexing start a concurrent indexing without cancelling the first one [#10581](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10581)

# Milestone
https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/milestone/417?closed=1


